CatDescriptText: Cutline of related images published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June 2, 1962, pg. 1, reads: "Scranton - Van Zandt Want Negro Vote; Will Wage All-Out Campaign to Get It... - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Three men, including Pennsylvania gubernatorial candidate William "Bill" Scranton and Mr. Wright, seated on sofa with sign on mantel reading "Pennsylvania needs Bill Scranton for Governor," for Republican banquet at Loendi Club
